From ea819c9ad13b5abab8c3d65d7a1f5edbfdbb5a93 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: poeggi <48416618+poeggi@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Sat, 13 Jun 2026 09:26:48 +0400
Subject: [PATCH 1/3] feat: stable MAC-based UUID v5 for ONVIF device identity
 (GetEndpointReference)

Generate a deterministic UUID v5 from the device's MAC address instead of
a random UUID.  The UUID is the same across reboots and satisfies the
WS-Discovery 1.1 requirement that the endpoint reference be stable.

Algorithm: SHA-1 of (DNS_NAMESPACE_UUID + "mac:xx:xx:xx:xx:xx:xx") per
RFC 4122, using the same MAC that auto-detection already resolved.

Changes:
  utils.c: add SHA-1 (RFC 3174) helpers and gen_uuid_v5_mac(); the helpers
    are named hash_uuid5_* to make their purpose explicit and to signal
    they are NOT suitable for general-purpose cryptographic use.
  utils.h: declare gen_uuid_v5_mac().
  conf.c: call gen_uuid_v5_mac() after address/ifs resolution; result stored
    in service_ctx.device_uuid.  Falls back to random UUID if MAC is
    unavailable.
  onvif_simple_server.h: add device_uuid[37] field to service_context_t.
  onvif_simple_server.c: dispatch GetEndpointReference.
  device_service.c / device_service.h: implement device_get_endpoint_reference().
  device_service_files/GetEndpointReference.xml: SOAP response template.
  wsd_simple_server.c: remove local static SHA-1 / UUID / gen_uuid_v5_mac
    block -- these are now provided by utils.c.
